    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Small Christian devotional statues that are typically carried as amulets in a pocket or elsewhere on a person's clothing. For items having a similar function but in the shape of a disc, use "devotional tokens."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079429/Daleiden, Official Catholic Directory (1928)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079245/Catholic Encyclopedia [online] (2003-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Devotieobject van slechts enkele centimeters groot, dat ter bescherming in de zak van jurk of pak werd gedragen. Bestaande uit een kleine houder met een heiligenbeeldje of een klein doosje met een of meer amuletten.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
